**![](data:image/png;base64,)**

This feature allows you to retrieve and visualize usage statistics for the attributes in the project.

- Click on **Retrieve usage statistics **in the **Reference data **tab or in the top bar.

![](data:image/png;base64,) 

![](data:image/png;base64,) 

The process starts:

![](data:image/png;base64,) 

- When the process ends, a message is displayed:

![](data:image/png;base64,) 

![](data:image/png;base64,) 

- Click on the **Copy **icon next to the **Retrieve Usage statistics **button to copy the resulting CSV ( tab-delimited file with double quotes as qualifier ) on the Clipboard

![](data:image/png;base64,) 

- The following popup appears:

![](data:image/png;base64,) 

- You can now open a text editor and paste it in.

- Select a highlighted attribute to view its statistics.

The numbers in brackets indicate the occurrences.

- The numbers in brackets in the parents are the sum of occurrences in the descendants.

![](data:image/png;base64,)
